message.content:
The boot appears stuck - the same text has been showing for 20+ seconds. The extra blank lines in AUTOEXEC.BAT might be causing issues. Let me fix and restart.

{
  "analysis": "The boot is stuck showing the same VGA text for 35+ seconds. The AUTOEXEC.BAT has extra blank lines from the heredoc which may be causing command parsing issues. Need to create a clean AUTOEXEC.BAT without extra blank lines and restart.",
  "plan": "Create a clean AUTOEXEC.BAT with no extra blank lines, kill QEMU, restart and monitor boot progress.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "printf '@ECHO OFF\\r\\nPROMPT $p$g\\r\\nPATH C:\\\\WINDOWS;C:\\\\DOS\\r\\nSET TEMP=C:\\\\TEMP\\r\\nwin\\r\\n' > /tmp/autoexec.bat\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mcopy -o -i /app/isos/win311.img@@32256 /tmp/autoexec.bat ::AUTOEXEC.BAT\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mtype -i /app/isos/win311.img@@32256 ::AUTOEXEC.BAT\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "kill $(pgrep qemu-system) 2>/dev/null; sleep 2; rm -f /tmp/qemu-monitor.sock\n",
      "duration": 5.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nohup qemu-system-i386 -m 32 -hda /app/isos/win311.img -snapshot -vnc :1 -monitor unix:/tmp/qemu-monitor.sock,server,nowait -vga cirrus -net nic,model=ne2k_isa -net user -boot c > /tmp/qemu.log 2>&1 &\necho \"PID: $!\"\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sleep 20 && python3 /tmp/read_vga.py\n",
      "duration": 25.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}
